result.execSummary:
The defendant Kenny W Kaminski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 11:05 am [Clerk SH] (Case was scheduled for FSSC)
[Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for Branch IV]
Defendant Kenny W Kaminski in court. ADA Theresa A Beck appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Mr. Kaminski submits plea questionnaire & waiver of right to counsel
ADA Beck submits victim impact statement & criminal case settlement

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

Court sentences the Defendant to pay a fine of $200 + costs = $705 (includes DNA Surcharge) + $100 domestic abuse surcharge = $805; due in $80 incriments per month, beginning 5/21/15 and on the 21st day of the month until paid in full. Non-payment results in a 16 day jail term, with Huber privileges consecutive. 
Recess: 11:19 am
Jury trial on April 27, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Final status/scheduling conference on April 21, 2015 at 10:30 am.

Case called at 2:48 pm [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Kenny W Kaminski in court. DA Susan Victoria Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Upon questioning of the Court, Mr. Kaminski indicates that he does not have counsel as he does not believe he needs counsel in this case
DA Happ provides Mr. Kaminski & Court with criminal case settlement form & offer of the State and informs the Court that Mr. Kaminski has turned down the FOP offer 
Court has further colloquy with Mr. Kaminski re: counsel/finances & choices of how to proceed with matter
Mr. Kaminski indicates that he may need attorney in this matter - Court has further colloquy with Mr. Kaminski re: finances, finds that he would not qualify for SPD Services - provides additional choices
Court confirms address on file is accurate for Mr. Kaminski & that his bond continues

Mr. Kaminski indicates that he would like to enter a plea in this case. Court directs Clerk to provide Mr. Kaminski plea paperwork
DA Happ presents concerns about factual basis due to some comments made by Mr. Kaminski, submits criminal case settlement
off-record: 3:01 - 3:05 pm for Court/DA Happ to reserach domestic abuse statutes for factual basis
Court/DA Happ review off-the-record discussions re: factual basis
Mr. Kaminski expresses alternating wishes re: entering a plea & wanting a trial date
Court presents basis, finds that Mr. Kaminski would not knowingly be able to enter plea at this time and informs parties that It will set matter for trial, finds good cause to set trial outside of 60 day time limit.
Recess: 3:13 pm
